					  <div class="accordion-body" itemprop="text">
						<span>
						<ul class="ul-circle">
							<li>
								<strong>Keyword rankings:</strong> We track the performance of targeted keywords in search engine rankings. If our SEO strategy is successful, you'll see your website moving up the ranks for these key search terms over time.
							</li>
							<li>
								<strong>Organic search traffic:</strong> The primary measure of SEO success is an increase in organic search traffic, which refers to visitors who reach your website through search engine results rather than through paid advertising. We use sophisticated analytics tools to track this data.
							</li>
							<li>
								<strong>Bounce rate:</strong> We measure the percentage of visitors who leave your website after viewing just one page. If the bounce rate is high, it can indicate that the content is not relevant or engaging to the visitors. SEO success should ideally reduce this rate.
							</li>
							<li>
								<strong>Conversion rate:</strong> SEO isn't just about driving more traffic to your site, but also about increasing the percentage of visitors who take a desired action, whether that's making a purchase, filling out a form, or signing up for a newsletter. This is called the conversion rate, and it's a key indicator of SEO success.
							</li>
							<li>
								<strong>Page loading time:</strong> Website speed is a critical factor in SEO. Thus, we measure the load time of your website and work to reduce it, offering a better user experience and helping your site rank higher in search results.
							</li>
							<li>
								<strong>Backlinks:</strong>
								<span style="font-weight: 400;">The nature of the links pointing to your site</span> can significantly impact your ranking performance—we monitor the number of backlinks and their quality.
							</li>
							<li>
								<strong>User engagement metrics:</strong> We assess user engagement, considering metrics like pages per session and average session duration. These indicate how well your audience finds your content valuable.
							</li>
							<li>
								<strong>Local visibility:</strong> If your business has a local component, we will also measure your visibility in local search results, tracking how well you're doing in Google's local listings.
							</li>
							<li>
								<strong>Mobile responsiveness:</strong> Mobile-friendliness is a significant factor in Google's ranking algorithm. Mindful of the ever-increasing use of smartphones for search, we ensure your site is mobile-ready.
							</li>
							<li>
								<strong>ROI:</strong> Ultimately, the best measure of SEO success is return on investment. We keep a close eye on your ROI, ensuring that your investment in SEO is delivering a profitable return.
							</li>
						</ul>
						<p>We continuously monitor these metrics and adjust our strategies based on what the data is telling us. Our focus is always on delivering meaningful results that contribute to your business goals.</p>
					</span>
