									<strong>Ahrefs:</strong> A powerful tool used for backlink analysis, competitor analysis, keyword research, and tracking keyword rankings.
								</li>
								<li>
									<strong>Google Analytics 4 (GA4):</strong> An indispensable tool for understanding website traffic, user behaviour, and conversions. We also use it to gauge the effectiveness of our SEO strategies over time.
								</li>
								<li>
									<strong>Google Search Console:</strong> We use this tool to understand how Google's search bots are interacting with your website, to identify crawl issues, and to submit sitemaps for indexing.
								</li>
								<li>
									<strong>Google My Business:</strong> A crucial tool for managing your online presence across Google, including Search and Maps. We can help you leverage this platform to its full potential, so that you can engage with customers, optimise your business profile, and gather insight about how people find your local business online.
								</li>
								<li>
									<strong>Screaming Frog SEO Spider:</strong> This is a website crawling tool that we use for technical SEO audits. It helps us to identify issues like broken links, duplicate content, and other potential problems.
								</li>
							</ul>
							<p>Each of these tools is applied in different ways throughout the various phases of an SEO campaign, including the initial audit, strategy development, execution, and ongoing optimisation and reporting. It's our combined use of these tools, backed by our expertise in SEO strategy and execution, that allows us to drive successful results for our clients.</p>
						</span>
					  </div>
