				  <div class="accordion-item" itemscope="" itemprop="mainEntity" >
					<h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingFour">
					  <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFour">
						<b itemprop="name"><span class="sr">04.</span>   What is off-page SEO?</b>
					  </button>
					</h2>
					<div id="collapseFour" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFour" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
						<div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" >
					  <div class="accordion-body" itemprop="text">
						<span>
	<p>The counterpart to on-page SEO, off-page SEO refers to actions taken outside of your own website to impact your rankings within search engine results pages (SERPs). Off-page SEO is a crucial part of any comprehensive SEO strategy, extending beyond the confines of your website to build its reputation and authority in the wider digital world.</p>
	<p>This section of SEO is primarily concerned with establishing and nurturing the presence and perception of your website in the online community. Pillars of a good off-page strategy might include any or all of the following.</p>
	<ul class="ul-circle">
		<li>
			<strong>Content marketing:</strong> Contributing high-quality content to other reputable sites can be a powerful off-page SEO technique. This not only exposes your brand to a broader audience but also allows you to gain valuable backlinks. It's essential to focus on creating valuable, informative content that aligns with the interests of the audience and the standards of the host site.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Social media engagement:</strong> While social media signals are not a direct ranking factor in most search engines, they play a crucial role in off-page SEO. Active engagement on social media platforms can increase your content's reach and visibility, leading to more traffic to your site and potentially more backlinks. It's about creating shareable content and fostering a community around your brand.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Backlink strategy.</strong> A cornerstone of off-page SEO is building a strong profile of backlinks. These are links from other websites that direct users to your site. Each backlink acts as a 'vote of confidence' from one site to another, signaling to search engines that your content is valuable and trustworthy. However, it's not just about quantity; the quality of backlinks matters significantly. Links from reputable and relevant sites carry more weight and contribute more positively to your site's SEO.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Online reputation management:</strong> How your brand is perceived online can significantly impact your SEO. This includes managing reviews and feedback across various platforms, including Google My Business, Yelp, and industry-specific review sites. Positive reviews can improve your brand's credibility and authority, contributing positively to your SEO efforts.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Local SEO tactics:</strong> For businesses with a physical presence, local SEO is a vital part of off-page optimisation. This includes optimising your Google My Business profile and getting listed in local directories. Local backlinks and reviews can significantly enhance your visibility in local search results.
		</li>
	</ul>
	<p>Off-page SEO is designed to complement on-page SEO efforts and is essential for a well-rounded SEO strategy. This multi-faceted approach lets us ensure that your website not only appeals to search engines but also resonates with your audience, ultimately driving organic traffic and elevating your online presence.</p>
</span>
					  </div>
						</div>
					</div>
				  </div>
				  </div>
				  				
				  <div class="col-sm-6">
	
				  <div class="accordion-item" itemscope="" itemprop="mainEntity" >
					<h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingFive">
					  <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFive" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFive">
						<b itemprop="name"><span class="sr">05.</span>   How long does it take to see results from an SEO campaign? </b>
					  </button>
					</h2>
					<div id="collapseFive" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFive" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
						<div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" >
					  <div class="accordion-body" itemprop="text">
						<span>
	<p>
		<span style="font-weight: 400;">There isn’t a hard-and-fast answer to this question. SEO represents a deliberate, long-term investment in your business’s marketing, and it tends to be about incremental gains over instant results. Variables like the general condition of your website, the industry you’re operating in, the competitive landscape, and the keywords targeted all come into play.&nbsp;</span>
	</p>
	<p>
		<span style="font-weight: 400;">To figure out what needs to be done, we start with a comprehensive examination of your website. This audit informs all our later strategy and recommendations and includes a thorough scan for technical issues, a review of your content to ensure alignment with SEO best practices, a detailed competitor analysis, and thorough keyword research and selection.</span>
	</p>
	<p>
		<span style="font-weight: 400;">After this phase is complete, the focus moves to an ongoing approach of monitoring and optimisation, including creation and fine-tuning of content, backlinking, and the ongoing application of technical SEO strategies.&nbsp;</span>
	</p>
	<p>
		<span style="font-weight: 400;">Initially, you may see small boosts to your rankings and organic traffic, but it’s important not to judge the entire campaign on these initial indicators. The compounding and incremental nature of SEO often means that the true rewards come later.&nbsp;</span>
	</p>
	<p>
		<span style="font-weight: 400;">To close the information gap while your campaign is running, XSTREAM INFOTECH provides regular, comprehensive reports containing key performance metrics and in-depth analysis. The data at the core of these reports is the same data we use to inform any fine-tuning to the campaign along with any recommendations we may have. As part of our commitment to transparency, we also run regular work-in-progress meetings, giving you an opportunity to discuss any aspects of the campaign.</span>
	</p>
	<p>
		<span style="font-weight: 400;">SEO isn’t a quick fix—instead, it aims to provide results in the longer term, securing better visibility for your website, pulling in better-quality traffic, and driving increases to sales, leads, and any other core KPIs you may have.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>
	</p>
</span>
					  </div>
						</div>
					</div>
				  </div>
				  <div class="accordion-item" itemscope="" itemprop="mainEntity" >
					<h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingSix">
					  <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseSix" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseSix">
